  "text": "More generally, our work also relates to the strand of literature considering the role of networks in reducing information costs associated with international trade (e.g. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In our view, the role of ISO 9000 for international trade very much overlaps with the role of ethnic Chinese networks for trade studied by [CITATION_3] . To the extent that ISO 9000 lowers information and search costs, it also relates to the role of Internet for trade studied by [CITATION_4] . Neither of these studies, however, discusses the potential endogeneity of networks' formation.",
